      </div>
      <hr/>
      <p>
       For the
						Spring 2019, this form will be available until
						Friday,
						04/19/2019.
      </p>
      <p>
       Students may request exam excuses in person until
						Friday,
						04/26/2019
						at UNC Academic Advising during
       <a href="http://advising.unc.edu/see-an-advisor/#drop-in" target="blank">
        drop-in hours
       </a>
       .
      </p>
      <p>
       Use this form only if you meet the following criteria:
      </p>
      <ul>
       <li>
        Your primary major is within the College of Arts and
							Sciences.
       </li>
       <li>
        You have two final exams scheduled at the same time or
							three exams which start within one 24 hour period (ie, 8am – 8am,
							noon-noon, etc).
       </li>
       <li>
        You have approved ARS accommodations impacting your
							overall testing time and know the details of your accommodations.
       </li>
       <li>
        None of the courses involved in the conflict are online
							courses and/or have ‘TBA’ listed for the class time (see UNC
							Advising during
        <a href="http://advising.unc.edu/see-an-advisor/#drop-in" target="blank">
         drop-in hours
        </a>
        for conflicts involving ‘TBA’
							classes).
       </li>
       <li>
        You know which exam you wish to move. Per UNC policy, if
							one of your courses is listed in the final exam schedule under
							the section for common hour exams, then the excuse must be used
							for that class.
       </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
       Exam time references:
      </p>
      <ul>
       <li>
        <a href="https://registrar.unc.edu/academic-calendar/part-time-classroom-studies-exam-schedule/" target="blank">
         Part-time Studies Exam Schedule
        </a>
        (for evening courses with a section number of ‘951’).
       </li>
       <li>
        <a href="https://registrar.unc.edu/academic-calendar/final-examination-schedule-spring/" target="blank">
         Registrar’s Final Exam Schedule
        </a>
        (for most on-campus classes).
       </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
       All other requests must be handled either by Campus Health (in
						case of documented illness) or by visiting UNC Academic Advising
						during
       <a href="http://advising.unc.edu/see-an-advisor/#drop-in" target="blank">
        drop-in hours
       </a>
       .
      </p>
      <p>
       For more information, consult the official
       <a href="http://catalog.unc.edu/policies-procedures/attendance-grading-examination/#text" target="blank">
        UNC Final Exam Excuse Policy.
       </a>
      </p>
      <h4>
       Log in to submit an Exam Excuse request
      </h4>
      <a class="btn btn-primary" href="home">
       Click to log in with
					Onyen
      </a>
